11. Bxe6
12. Ng5 {The critical continuation, trying to win a pawn.} 
12. Bd5
13. Nxh7
13. Rxh7 {The key.} 
14. Bxh7
14. g6 {It turns out White's bishop is trapped, and Black is fine in all lines.} 
15. d4
15. Nd7 {15...cxd3?16.h4and we do not have ...Bh6 like on move 15 in the previous variation.} 
16. Bg5
16. e6
17. f4 {17.Nd2Be718.h4Bxg519.hxg5Ne7,followed by ...Nf8 next.} 
17. Be7
18. h4
18. Nf8
19. Bg8
19. Nd7
20. Bh7
20. Nf8 {A strange repetition ends the game.} 
