14. d4
14. Bd6 {I like Fedorov's move, as the bishop is more active on d6.14...Be7is very similar and is the move correspondence players prefer, but14...Bd6leads to more interesting play. I want you to remember the following idea, which is very typical in this variation.} 
15. Bd3
15. O-O
16. Be3
16. f5
17. exf5 {Now, Fedorov played17...Ne7?!and won a complex struggle after18.fxe6Bxf319.gxf3dxe6, but it is better and much more instructive to play the text move.} 
17. Rxf5
18. Bxf5
18. Qxf5 {Black has enormous compensation for the exchange, as all of our pieces are in very active positions.} 
