11. Qc7 {White has now three different ways of protecting the h2-pawn. All of them lead to slightly different positions and it is not clear which one is best.} 
12. g3 {The most normal-looking move to my eyes, restricting the d6-bishop. I know it sounds crazy, but we can actually get counterplay thanks to this slight weakening of the h1-a8 diagonal.} 
12. O-O
13. a3
13. b5
14. Nd2
14. Bb7
15. c4
15. Be5
16. Bxe5
16. Nxe5
17. cxb5
17. axb5
